<taxonomicName authorityName="M. R. Henderson" authorityYear="1933" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus tortilipetalus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tortilipetalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus tortilipetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all of which form a monophyletic group (
<bibRefCitation author="Nakkuntod, M" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="127 - 132" refId="B11" refString="Nakkuntod, M, Su, YC, Seelanan, T, Saunders, RMK, 2009. Molecular phylogenetic and morphological evidence for the congeneric status of Goniothalamus and Richella (Annonaceae). Taxon 58 (1): 127 - 132" title="Molecular phylogenetic and morphological evidence for the congeneric status of Goniothalamus and Richella (Annonaceae)." volume="58" year="2009">Nakkuntod et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and are characterized by relatively large sepals with distinct veins and stamens with long apiculate connectives (
<bibRefCitation author="Saunders, RMK" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="355 - 384" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1095-8339.2007.00762.x" refId="B14" refString="Saunders, RMK, Chalermglin, P, 2008. A synopsis of Goniothalamus species (Annonaceae) in Thailand, with descriptions of three new species. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 156 (3): 355 - 384, DOI: 10.1111/j.1095-8339.2007.00762.x" title="A synopsis of Goniothalamus species (Annonaceae) in Thailand, with descriptions of three new species." url="10.1111/j.1095-8339.2007.00762.x" volume="156" year="2008">Saunders and Chalermglin 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Among the three species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus flagellistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. R. Henderson" authorityYear="1933" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus tortilipetalus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tortilipetalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus tortilipetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is distributed in the Malay Peninsula, in having more than 200 stamens and more than 50 carpels. In fact, The BLAST similarity search based on the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">matK</emphasis>
sequence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus flagellistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resulted in homology as high as 734/736 bp with the sequence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. R. Henderson" authorityYear="1933" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus tortilipetalus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tortilipetalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus tortilipetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(GeneBank accession no. EU715081) in the DNA database. However, as described in the diagnosis above, the two species can be easily distinguished by the number of stamens and carpels per flower, and style length (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between Goniothalamus flagellistylus sp. nov. and Goniothalamus tortilipetalus (modified from Henderson 1933; Saunders 2003; Saunders and Chalermglin 2008)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3B8CB6615ABE3347CEE8EDC0578264F9" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" tableUuid="3B8CB6615ABE3347CEE8EDC0578264F9">1</tableCitation>
). Also, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus flagellistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. R. Henderson" authorityYear="1933" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus tortilipetalus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tortilipetalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus tortilipetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that flowers arise not only from the main trunk but also from the older branches as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Craib" authorityYear="1922" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus calvicarpus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calvicarpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus calvicarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker f. &amp; Thomson" authorityYear="1855" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus griffithii" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goniothalamus griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Saunders, RMK" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="355 - 384" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1095-8339.2007.00762.x" refId="B14" refString="Saunders, RMK, Chalermglin, P, 2008. A synopsis of Goniothalamus species (Annonaceae) in Thailand, with descriptions of three new species. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 156 (3): 355 - 384, DOI: 10.1111/j.1095-8339.2007.00762.x" title="A synopsis of Goniothalamus species (Annonaceae) in Thailand, with descriptions of three new species." url="10.1111/j.1095-8339.2007.00762.x" volume="156" year="2008">Saunders and Chalermglin 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
