<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Data deficient. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="5" start="start">Goniothalamus</pageBreakToken>
flagellistylus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a single population, including only six individuals: only one produces flowers/fruits while the others are just saplings. This situation satisfies the CR (critically endangered) status in criterion D of IUCN Red List Categories (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Cay Co Viet Nam: An Illustrated Flora of Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org" refId="B6" refString="IUCN, 2014. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2014.3., http://www.iucnredlist.org [accessed 30.01.2015]" title="The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2014.3" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org" year="2014">IUCN 2014</bibRefCitation>
). However, more individuals could be found if neighboring areas are more thoroughly surveyed. Thus, we regard the conservation status as DD. In Mt. Hon Ba, large areas of primary evergreen forest below 300-400 m elevation had been cleared or selectively logged before the Hon Ba Nature Reserve established, and it is likely that some habitats of this species were lost. The forest habitat where we found 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Goniothalamus flagellistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains less disturbed under a lower level of logging activities probably because of its landform of the steep slope near the rapid river. The forest in this Nature Reserve is currently protected well from anthropogenic activities, and recovering better and better. The current data available are not enough for a risk evaluation, we therefore need special attention to the individuals/populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniothalamus flagellistylus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flagellistylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Goniothalamus flagellistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
